snippet: Instead of fresh faces, many of the recently elected members of the House of Representatives are career bureaucrats and policy wonks with deep histories in politics and government.
abstract: Many of the recently elected members of the House of Representatives have deep career histories in politics and government;  they make up what could be characterized as an 'anti-antigovernment wave' in a Congress more volatile than any seen in 20 years.
lead_paragraph: Instead of fresh faces, many of the recently elected members of the House of Representatives are career bureaucrats and policy wonks with deep histories in politics and government.

headline.seo: Election Brings Seasoned Politicians to Congress
headline.main: 113th Congress: This Time, It’s Out With the New
headline.print_headline: In New House, A Political Past Is Actually O.K.
